    "media:imagetext": "TWA\nEMPLOYEES' TIMETABLE • DOMESTIC SCHEDULES\nISSUE DATE MAY 3, 1974\nEFFECTIVE JUNE 15, 1974\n(Except as Noted)\nThis timetable is being issued to reflect the addition of new mileage and seasonal increases as allowed under capacity agree-\nments in the following markets:\nNYC-LAX, NYC-SFO, ORD-SFO, WAS-LAX, NYC-DEN, PHL-SFO, WAS-LAX, WAS-DEN,\nNYC-DEN.\nTime and equipment changes are also being made for marketing and operational improvement. Major schedule\nactions are listed below.\nNEW NARROWBODY SERVICE\nJFK-DEN Flights 155/156\nORD-LAS Flights 139/6711/262\nIAD-DEN Flights 211/212\nORD-TUS Flights 179/106\nLAS-STL E/B only Flight 432\nICT-LAX-SFO Flights 295/296\nPIT-DEN Flights 173/174\nORD-DEN Flights 265/162\nPHL-STL Flights 283/248\nSTL-DEN Flights 167/456\nJFK-IND-STL Flights 373/94\nDCA-ORD Flights 377/376\nORD-ICT Flights 343/330\nNEW WIDE BODY SERVICE\nPHL-SFO Flights 31/54 opt 1011 I.L.O. B-707\nNYC-SFO Flights 41/46 opt 1011 I.L.O. B-707\nWAS-LAX Flights 735/74 opt 1011 I.L.O. B-707\nPIT-ORD-SFO Flights 135/130 opt 1011 I.L.O. B-707\nORD-SFO Flights 175/82 opt 1011 I.L.O. B-707\nIND-STL-SFO Flights 223/446 effective July 15\nTWA FORM T211-5-74 PRINTED IN U.S.A.\nEMPLOYEES' TIMETABLE NO. 74-7\nCancels Employees' Timetable No. 74-6",
